                    </div>
                    <span>With no previous experience, I began construction of a log home in 1997.  I had conducted an extensive literature search prior to beginning the project and had purchase several of the major texts available.  After construction of the foundation and three courses of logs, I found "Log Construction Manual" by Robert Chambers.  For the remainder of the project I used "Log Construction Manual" as my primary reference.  The material is ourstanding, well written and complete.  His log selection method to control shoulder height is second to none. I highly recommend this publication.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">In need of update</div>
